ang Wang, Dabin Zheng, Cunsheng Ding | published=2021-01-21 | primary_category=cs.IT | id=2101.08425]\n\n=== openreview (5 results) ===\n  1. \n     https://openreview.net/forum?id=ITHTHybcCA\n     [authors= | rank=1 | id=ITHTHybcCA]\n  2. \n     https://openreview.net/forum?id=urkBQD94DS\n     [authors= | rank=2 | id=urkBQD94DS]\n  3. \n     https://openreview.net/forum?id=emwkgCLNBd\n     [authors= | rank=3 | id=emwkgCLNBd]\n  4. \n     https://openreview.net/forum?id=UCDoREV8M6\n     [authors= | rank=4 | id=UCDoREV8M6]\n  5. CLAP: Learning Transferable Binary Code Representations with Natural Language Supervision\n     https://openreview.net/forum?id=PMtc5cwkv8\n     [authors=Hao Wang, Zeyu Gao, Chao Zhang, Zihan Sha, Mingyang Sun, Yuchen Zhou, Wenyu Zhu, Wenju Sun, Han Qiu, Xi Xiao | rank=5 | id=PMtc5cwkv8]\n\n=== exa (5 results) ===\n  1. microsoft/CLAP: Learning audio concepts from natural ...\n     https://github.com/microsoft/CLAP\n     CLAP (Contrastive Language-Audio Pretraining) is a model that learns acoustic concepts from natural language supervision and enables “Zero-Shot” inference.\n  2. LAION-AI/CLAP: Contrastive Language-Audio Pretraining\n     https://github.com/LAION-AI/CLAP", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
